  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2005-09-29",
    "date": "2005-11-09T21:35:13Z",
    "text": "Small Business Fuel Cost Relief Act of 2005 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow certain commercial farmers, fishermen, and small business owners a temporary two-year business tax credit for excessive fuel cost (i.e., for gasoline, diesel fuel, heating oil, and natural gas. Defines \"excessive fuel cost\" as the amount currently paid for fuel over the Labor Day 2004 price for such fuel, adjusted for inflation.\n\nAllows taxpayers a standard automobile mileage allowance of 60 cents per mile in lieu of the tax credit provided by this Act."
  },
